HEADWORD: Marchioness
<hw>Mar"chion*ess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>marchionissa</ets>, fr. <ets>marchio</ets> a marquis. See
<ets>Marquis</ets>.]</ety> <def>The wife or the widow of a marquis; a
woman who has the rank and dignity of a marquis.</def>
<rj><au>Spelman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

